    "Explain Mixture of Experts like I'm 10<|assistant|Imagine a school where instead of one teacher who knows everything, you have 8 different teachers. One is great at math, one at art, one at music, etc.\n\nWhen you ask a question, a special 'decider' looks at your question and sends you to the 2 best teachers for that topic. If you ask about fractions, you go to the math teacher. If you ask about painting, you go to the art teacher.\n\nThat's MoE! The 'experts' are neural networks that specialize in different things, and the 'decider' (gate) routes each question to the right experts. This is faster and better than making one giant network do everything.",

